main event: Approximately 30 objects with red lights in a circular formation were observed moving from northeast to southwest in Staunton, Virginia in 1952.
interesting points: The report includes 6 photographs of the observed objects.
The objects were observed for a duration of 1 hour.
There was no established course for the objects.
Conclusions were reached stating that the objects were unidentified and not related to balloons, aircraft, or Venus.
An Air Force Lieutenant suggested the possibility of the objects being weather balloons lighted to be spotted with a theodolite.
